  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 5.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - This verse is repeated below (ver. 9). It comes in awkwardly here, interrupting the connection which subsists between vers. 4 and 6. Its right place is doubtless where it occurs below. The Law not only strictly forbade false witness (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 20:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 23:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), but it enacted severe penalties against offenders in this particular (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 19:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.); the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "lex",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "talionis",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " was to be enforced against them, they were to receive no pity: \"Life shall be for life, eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "He that",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "speaketh lies shall not escape.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The Septuagint confines the notion of this clause to false accusers, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Ὁ δὲ ἐγκαλῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀδίκως",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"He who maketh an unjust charge shall not escape,\" which renders the two clauses almost synonymous. We make a distinction between the members by seeing in the former a denunciation against a false witness in a suit, and in the second a more sweeping menace against any one, whether accuser, slanderer, sycophant, who by lying injures a neighbour. The History of Susanna is brought forward in confirmation of the well deserved fate of false accusers. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Ψευδὴς διαβολὴ τὸν βίον λυμαίνεται",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "\"A slander is an outrage on man's life.\"",
        "children": []
