        "text": "Proverbs 19:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we have the introductory proverb of two groups, the former of which, in its close as well as its beginning, cannot be mistaken.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "5 A lying witness remaineth not unpunished;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "   And he who breathes out lies escapeth not.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Regarding יפיח, vid., vol. i, p. 148: as here we read it of false witness at Proverbs 6:19; Proverbs 14:5, Proverbs 14:25. לא ינּקה occurs four times before, the last of which is at Proverbs 17:5. The lxx elsewhere translates יפיח כזבים by ἐκκαίειν ψευδῆ, to kindle lies; but here by ὁ δὲ ἐκαλῶν ἀδίκως, and at Proverbs 19:9 by ὃς δ ̓ ἂν ἐκκαύσῃ κακίαν, both times changing only because ψευδής goes before, and instead of ψευδῆ, the choice of a different rendering commended itself. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Regarding יפיח, vid., vol. i, p. 148: as here we read it of false witness at ",
            "children": []
